<div class=3D"post-block ">
  <div class=3D"constrain">
    <h2>IBU Ranges by Style</h2>
<p>Many beer drinkers have found that there=E2=80=99s a general IBU range t=
hey prefer, and styles of beer tend to fall within a particular IBU range. =
The list below identifies some common beer styles and their associated IBUs=
.</p>
<ul>
<li>Light Lager =E2=80=94 4-10</li>
<li>Blond Ale =E2=80=94 14-25</li>
<li>Saison =E2=80=94 20-38</li>
<li>Pilsner =E2=80=94 25-45</li>
<li>Dry Stout =E2=80=94 30-35</li>
<li>Pale Ale =E2=80=94 30-50</li>
<li>Hazy IPA =E2=80=94 30-50</li>
<li>Hazy Double IPA =E2=80=94 45-80</li>
<li>West Coast IPA =E2=80=94 50-70</li>
<li>Imperial Stout =E2=80=94 50-80</li>
<li>Double IPA =E2=80=94 65-100</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

